The paper studies the complexity of linear sketching over $\mathbb F_2$ for Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also explores the connection between sketching complexity and Fourier sparsity, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds for a subclass of symmetric functions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
